list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: the rate at which something occurs or is repeated over a particular period of time or in a given sample.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: shops have closed with increasing frequency during the period
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Các cửa hàng đã đóng cửa với tần suất ngày càng tăng trong khoảng thời gian

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: the rate at which a vibration occurs that constitutes a wave, either in a material (as in sound waves), or in an electromagnetic field (as in radio waves and light), usually measured per second.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: different thicknesses of glass will absorb different frequencies of sound
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Độ dày khác nhau của kính sẽ hấp thụ các tần số khác nhau của âm thanh
